Function# sec_protocol_metadata_peers_are_equal(_:_:)

iOS 12.0+iPadOS 12.0+Mac Catalyst 13.1+macOS 10.14+tvOS 12.0+visionOS 1.0+watchOS 5.0+

```
func sec_protocol_metadata_peers_are_equal(
    _ metadataA: sec_protocol_metadata_t,
    _ metadataB: sec_protocol_metadata_t
) -> Bool
```

## [ Parameters ](/documentation/Security/sec_protocol_metadata_peers_are_equal(_:_:)#parameters)

`metadataA`A `sec_protocol_metadata_t` instance.

`metadataB`A `sec_protocol_metadata_t` instance.

## [Return Value](/documentation/Security/sec_protocol_metadata_peers_are_equal(_:_:)#return-value)

Returns true if both metadata values refer to the same peer, and false otherwise.

## [Discussion](/documentation/Security/sec_protocol_metadata_peers_are_equal(_:_:)#discussion)

Compare peer information for two `sec_protocol_metadata` instances. This comparison does not include protocol configuration options, e.g., ciphersuites.
